```

**Fix:** Data should come from a database or environment-injected configuration — never from source literals in production code:

```js
// ✅ Data comes from the database layer
app.get('/users', requireAuth, async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const users = await db.query('SELECT id, name, email FROM users');
    res.json(users);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err); // Forwarded to error handler (see below)
  }
});
```

